{
  "stem": "3085.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because she had that idea if you're less than 10 years old, you'll be treated better.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Now-- [LAUGHS] so we actually, throughout our stay in Auschwitz, we were known as nine-year-olds.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We were-- because we didn't, of course, dare to later on reveal that it's a lie.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So when we were told to tell our birth date, we changed from 1933 to 1935.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we stayed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And all our friends, all our-- all the other twins, of course, in, in-- they didn't know that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We were-- we were considered pretty smart for nine-year-olds, [LAUGHS] which was kind of an advantage in some ways.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But that was because my mother told us not to say we're 11, in case we're asked.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But to get back to that point, we, we were at that point separated.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never saw my mother and sister again.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I never heard of them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I never saw them again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, and I must assume-- and it's strictly an assumption on my part, that they perished on that same day.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when it comes to their yahrzeit, we [CRYING] actually commemorate that day, which is July 9th, 1944.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[CRYING] It's, it's the-- in, in Hebrew date, it's the 18th of Tammuz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we use the 18th of Tammuz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we have absolutely no idea whether, in fact, that was the date.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we-- that's-- it's just-- [CRYING] you have to pick a date.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's when we were taken over-- [CRYING] we were taken over to another-- some barracks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and, and actually, we were taken by ambulance, I think, to-- there was an ambulance nearby, an ambulance car.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were taken by ambulance to a-- to a-- an area which turned out to be the, the camp for the-- for the twins.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
